    How are other sites addressing these issues?  My personal inclination
    is "Damn the torpedoes, full speed ahead"-- we should ignore the problems
    of hosttable-only sites and put the compatibility burden on them,
    in hopes that they will become fewer and fewer.

We obviously have to use domain names because we aren't in the hosttable.
And hiding behind other hosts (like mit-eddie.arpa or csnet-relay.arpa)
probably wouldn't be appreciated.  Even if we had the option, however,
we would still use domain names in the hopes of `encouraging' stragglers
to catch up...

-Philip

